<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"><meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge"><meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no" name="viewport"><link type="text/css" rel="stylesheet" href="_TheLordTitlesAndRL.css" /></head><body>

<div class="c240_29"> 
<div id="v240.29.1"><span class="H376 s">He</span><span class="H8433 s">, that being often reproved</span><span class="H7185 s"> hardeneth</span><span class="H6203 s"> <i>his</i> neck</span><span class="H6621 s">, shall suddenly</span><span class="H7665 s"> be destroyed</span><span class="H4832 s">, and that without remedy</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (He…: Heb. A man of reproofs)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.29.2"><span class="H6662 s">When the righteous</span><span class="H7235 s"> are in authority</span><span class="H5971 s">, the people</span><span class="H8055 s"> rejoice</span><span class="H7563 s">: but when the wicked</span><span class="H4910 s"> beareth rule</span><span class="H5971 s">, the people</span><span class="H584 s"> mourn</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (in…: or, increased)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.29.3"><span class="H376 s">Whoso</span><span class="H157 s"> loveth</span><span class="H2451 s"> wisdom</span><span class="H8055 s"> rejoiceth</span><span class="H1 s"> his father</span><span class="H7462 s">: but he that keepeth company</span><span class="H2181 s"> with harlots</span><span class="H6 s"> spendeth</span><span class="H1952 s"> <i>his</i> substance</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.4"><span class="H4428 s">The king</span><span class="H4941 s"> by judgment</span><span class="H5975 s"> establisheth</span><span class="H776 s"> the land</span><span class="H376 s">: but he</span><span class="H8641 s"> that receiveth gifts</span><span class="H2040 s"> overthroweth</span> it. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (he…: Heb. a man of oblations)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.29.5"><span class="H1397 s">A man</span><span class="H2505 s"> that flattereth</span><span class="H7453 s"> his neighbour</span><span class="H6566 s"> spreadeth</span><span class="H7568 s"> a net</span><span class="H6471 s"> for his feet</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.6"><span class="H6588 s">In the transgression</span><span class="H7451 s"> of an evil</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span><span class="H4170 s"> <i>there is</i> a snare</span><span class="H6662 s">: but the righteous</span><span class="H7442 s"> doth sing</span><span class="H8056 s"> and rejoice</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.7"><span class="H6662 s">The righteous</span><span class="H3045 s"> considereth</span><span class="H1779 s"> the cause</span><span class="H1800 s"> of the poor</span><span class="H7563 s">: <i>but</i> the wicked</span><span class="H995 s"> regardeth</span><span class="H1847 s"> not to know</span> <i>it</i>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.8"><span class="H3944 s">Scornful</span><span class="H582 s"> men</span><span class="H6315 s"> bring</span><span class="H7151 s"> a city</span><span class="H6315 s"> into a snare</span><span class="H2450 s">: but wise</span><span class="H7725 s"> <i>men</i> turn away</span><span class="H639 s"> wrath</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (bring…: or, set a city on fire)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.29.9"><span class="H2450 s"><i>If</i> a wise</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span><span class="H8199 s"> contendeth</span><span class="H191 s"> with a foolish</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span><span class="H7264 s">, whether he rage</span><span class="H7832 s"> or laugh</span><span class="H5183 s">, <i>there is</i> no rest</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.10"><span class="H582 s">The bloodthirsty</span><span class="H1818 s"> †</span><span class="H8130 s"> hate</span><span class="H8535 s"> the upright</span><span class="H3477 s">: but the just</span><span class="H1245 s"> seek</span><span class="H5315 s"> his soul</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (The bloodthirsty: Heb. Men of blood)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.29.11"><span class="H3684 s">A fool</span><span class="H3318 s"> uttereth</span><span class="H7307 s"> all his mind</span><span class="H2450 s">: but a wise</span><span class="H7623 s"> <i>man</i> keepeth</span><span class="H268 s"> it in till afterwards</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.12"><span class="H4910 s">If a ruler</span><span class="H7181 s"> hearken</span><span class="H1697 s"> to lies</span><span class="H8267 s"> †</span><span class="H8334 s">, all his servants</span><span class="H7563 s"> <i>are</i> wicked</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.13"><span class="H7326 s">The poor</span><span class="H8501 s"> and the deceitful</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span><span class="H6298 s"> meet together</span><span class="H3068 s">: the LORD</span><span class="H215 s"> lighteneth</span><span class="H8147 s"> both</span><span class="H5869 s"> their eyes</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the deceitful…: or, the usurer)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.29.14"><span class="H4428 s">The king</span><span class="H571 s"> that faithfully</span><span class="H8199 s"> judgeth</span><span class="H1800 s"> the poor</span><span class="H3678 s">, his throne</span><span class="H3559 s"> shall be established</span><span class="H5703 s"> for ever</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.15"><span class="H7626 s">The rod</span><span class="H8433 s"> and reproof</span><span class="H5414 s"> give</span><span class="H2451 s"> wisdom</span><span class="H5288 s">: but a child</span><span class="H7971 s"> left</span><span class="H517 s"> <i>to himself</i> bringeth his mother</span><span class="H954 s"> to shame</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.16"><span class="H7563 s">When the wicked</span><span class="H7235 s"> are multiplied</span><span class="H6588 s">, transgression</span><span class="H7235 s"> increaseth</span><span class="H6662 s">: but the righteous</span><span class="H7200 s"> shall see</span><span class="H4658 s"> their fall</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.17"><span class="H3256 s">Correct</span><span class="H1121 s"> thy son</span><span class="H5117 s">, and he shall give thee rest</span><span class="H5414 s">; yea, he shall give</span><span class="H4574 s"> delight</span><span class="H5315 s"> unto thy soul</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.18"><span class="H2377 s">Where <i>there is</i> no vision</span><span class="H5971 s">, the people</span><span class="H6544 s"> perish</span><span class="H8104 s">: but he that keepeth</span><span class="H8451 s"> the law</span><span class="H835 s">, happy</span> <i>is</i> he. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (perish: or, is made naked)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.29.19"><span class="H5650 s">A servant</span><span class="H3256 s"> will not be corrected</span><span class="H1697 s"> by words</span><span class="H995 s">: for though he understand</span><span class="H4617 s"> he will not answer</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.20"><span class="H2372 s">Seest</span><span class="H376 s"> thou a man</span><span class="H213 s"> <i>that is</i> hasty</span><span class="H1697 s"> in his words</span><span class="H8615 s">? <i>there is</i> more hope</span><span class="H3684 s"> of a fool</span> than of him. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (words: or, matters?)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.29.21"><span class="H6445 s">He that delicately bringeth up</span><span class="H5650 s"> his servant</span><span class="H5290 s"> from a child</span><span class="H4497 s"> shall have him become <i>his</i> son</span><span class="H319 s"> at the length</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.22"><span class="H639 s">An angry</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span><span class="H1624 s"> stirreth up</span><span class="H4066 s"> strife</span><span class="H2534 s">, and a furious</span><span class="H1167 s"> man</span><span class="H7227 s"> aboundeth in</span><span class="H6588 s"> transgression</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.23"><span class="H120 s">A man's</span><span class="H1346 s"> pride</span><span class="H8213 s"> shall bring him low</span><span class="H3519 s">: but honour</span><span class="H8551 s"> shall uphold</span><span class="H8217 s"> the humble</span><span class="H7307 s"> in spirit</span>.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.24"><span class="H2505 s">Whoso is partner</span><span class="H1590 s"> with a thief</span><span class="H8130 s"> hateth</span><span class="H5315 s"> his own soul</span><span class="H8085 s">: he heareth</span><span class="H423 s"> cursing</span><span class="H5046 s">, and bewrayeth</span> <i>it</i> not.</div> 
<div id="v240.29.25"><span class="H2731 s">The fear</span><span class="H120 s"> of man</span><span class="H5414 s"> bringeth</span><span class="H4170 s"> a snare</span><span class="H982 s">: but whoso putteth his trust</span><span class="H3068 s"> in the LORD</span><span class="H7682 s"> shall be safe</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (safe: Heb. set on high)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.29.26"><span class="H7227 s">Many</span><span class="H1245 s"> seek</span><span class="H4910 s"> the ruler's</span><span class="H6440 s"> favour</span><span class="H376 s">; but <i>every</i> man's</span><span class="H4941 s"> judgment</span><span class="H3068 s"> <i>cometh</i> from the LORD</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (the ruler's…: Heb. the face of a ruler)</span></div> 
<div id="v240.29.27"><span class="H5766 s">An unjust</span><span class="H376 s"> man</span><span class="H8441 s"> <i>is</i> an abomination</span><span class="H6662 s"> to the just</span><span class="H3477 s">: and <i>he that is</i> upright</span><span class="H1870 s"> in the way</span><span class="H8441 s"> <i>is</i> abomination</span><span class="H7563 s"> to the wicked</span>.</div></div>

